<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20532] The property cassandra.streaming.session.parallelTransfers is partly ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20532</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The property is ignored when it comes to create the semaphore used to control the streaming slots used, where it is always created using the default size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, the netty pool for the transfers is sized accordingly if the property is defined.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is a trivial one-line change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-4.1.8/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/streaming/async/StreamingMultiplexedChannel.java#L98&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;StreamingMultiplexedChannel.java&lt;/a&gt; ( v4.1+)&#160;or &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-4.0.17/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/streaming/async/NettyStreamingMessageSender.java#L92&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;NettyStreamingMessageSender.java&lt;/a&gt; ( v4.0 ) where the semaphore size has to be changed from &lt;tt&gt;DEFAULT_MAX_PARALLEL_TRANSFERS&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;MAX_PARALLEL_TRANSFERS&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
